  "problem": {
    "description": "You are given a binary array nums containing only the integers 0 and 1. Return the number of subarrays in nums that have more 1's than 0's. Since the answer may be very large, return it modulo 109 + 7.\nA subarray is a contiguous sequence of elements within an array.\n \nExample 1:\n\nInput: nums = [0,1,1,0,1]\nOutput: 9\nExplanation:\nThe subarrays of size 1 that have more ones than zeros are: [1], [1], [1]\nThe subarrays of size 2 that have more ones than zeros are: [1,1]\nThe subarrays of size 3 that have more ones than zeros are: [0,1,1], [1,1,0], [1,0,1]\nThe subarrays of size 4 that have more ones than zeros are: [1,1,0,1]\nThe subarrays of size 5 that have more ones than zeros are: [0,1,1,0,1]\n\nExample 2:\n\nInput: nums = [0]\nOutput: 0\nExplanation:\nNo subarrays have more ones than zeros.\n\nExample 3:\n\nInput: nums = [1]\nOutput: 1\nExplanation:\nThe subarrays of size 1 that have more ones than zeros are: [1]\n\n \nConstraints:\n\n1 <= nums.length <= 105\n0 <= nums[i] <= 1\n\n"
  },
